76561198091474445,Recommended,214340,32649443,Posted: 22 June,all,galstore8642,"This is a fun game to play.  The graphics are excellent and the dialog is amusing and very well thought out.  The puzzle aspect of the game is also good.  As far as difficulty, I would say it's challenging, but not impossible to figure out.  Patience is a virtue in this game.  I have not played puzzle games very much though.  The game mechanics perform well (except for what is said below).  There are a couple of things I wish it had.  Hints would be nice (none that I saw).  The interaction beteeen the mouse and the screen is not very good sometimes.  I have a brand new mouse and computer, so don't believe it's my equipment's fault.  By interaction, I  mean that you have to click on an object three or four times just to to use it.  Once selected, it takes another three or four times to actually use it.  For example, I wanted to take the socks out of my inventory and put them in the boiling water per the video clip I watched, could not do it.  I also wish it had a resolution option for 2560 x 1440.  Other than that, I would recommend this game.  It was well worth the money and I would buy it again.  Kudos to the game developer."
76561197968514473,Recommended,214340,18372142,"Posted: 7 October, 2015",all,Meat-King©®,"""Everything you do will end in chaos.""Deponia is a point & click adventure and the first of a three-part series developed by the company Daedalic Entertainment with emphasis on character and story development.Atmosphere & presentation:+ Original ideas and well-animated comic look create an interesting world.+ Creative puzzle sections with interesting solutions throughout the game.o Solid musical background.o Complex puzzles can be skipped.- The sometimes illogical item combinations can lead to a break in immersion.Characters & story:+ Surprising and refreshing depiction of side characters.+ Witty dialogues and unconventional conversation options.+ Coherent and fluid story telling.+ High quality voice acting.o Characterization of the protagonist can be polarizing at certain points.o Based on the German origin of the game, some of the jokes are lost in translation.- The partially sexist jokes of the protagonist could be considered inappropriate for the younger audience.Summary:The debut of Daedalic Entertainment represents a good start of the trilogy offering a multitude of original ideas, which make Deponia well worth playing.Achievements:Estimated time for 100 % completion: +10 hoursSingleplayer achievements: 19Multiplayer achievements: none"
