76561198043284605,Not Recommended,214340,8746521,"Posted: 17 January, 2014",all,RosarioLuigi,"The ""point-and-click-adventure"" aspects are done pretty well although some puzzles come down to plain guess work and in a game of this type there should always be some clues - even if you have to dig deep for them.  Overall, that section of the game is more good than bad.The rest of the game is in its dialogue and ""humor.""  This is all just opinion but I found the game and its main character to be crass, vulgar, lewd, rude, offensive, egotistical and just all-around someone I would not want to know.  Since the game relies on its humor as a form of charm - and I must posit that the developers misread the definition of charm - I must give the game a bad review.  Being stuck in the shoes of Rufus for several hours was an unpleasant experience at best.  The Droggeljug mode that you unlock via game completion is just mind-jarringly awful - every line of dialogue is replaced by, ""droggeljug"".I'm a bit of a curmudgeon though so at the same time, if you like this type of game, give it a shot - perhaps you will like the humor more than I."
