76561198073600298,Not Recommended,214340,18377150,"Posted: 7 October, 2015",all,Legacy,"A cartoon looking point and click adventure game that allows you to take control of Rufus, a dimwit jerk who uses everyone around him without care.The story starts off slow and begins to pick up a little bit as you reach the middle of the game, but I still found it lacking even 5 hours in. You play as Rufus, a selfish and slightly empty minded tinkerer who wishes only to leave the junkyard he calls home. Well, the planet he lives on is a junkyard.Did you know if you double click a location you don't have to walk to it? I didn't, you should probably do the tutorial.I found the characters hard to like and the protagonist even harder to enjoy. He acts like a childish pig and makes for really cringe dialogue when talking to his ex girlfriend. I also found that there was too much highlight on the protagonist, making you fall out of the story every time he opens his mouth.The puzzles follow little logic, often being very hard to follow and require the use of a walkthrough if you don't want to go insane. I've found many other reviews complain about this problem too, and it really put me off.I found trying to finish this game was a chore.It does have neat steampunk graphics that are fun to look at, and silly humour that will give you a little giggle here and there. The music is also pretty decent for an indie game.Save often, as this game bugs out every so often ending you not being to move or just plain out interact with items.I got it on sale, and I would recommend avoiding the full price as the game is too short (around 8-10 hours for first playthrough) and has little replayability.Personal Rating: 2/5"
,Recommended,214340,31589861,Posted: 6 May,all,Springorchid,"I'm playing Deponia in English and although it's a German game, English seems to be perfect in voice acting, and never fails to make humorous word plays.I first got to know about Daedalic through Edna&Harvey: Harvey's new eyes (Yes I played the spin-off first) and absolutely loved it. So I tried Deponia, as it was in the bundle I bought, and loved it too. I couldn't wait to buy the next episodes as I finished Deponia.I can't say whether the same sound effects and songs from Edna&Harvey is a good thing or not. I think it really depends on the players. Some fans might like the fact that they are indulged in the similar game chain of Daedalic, and some may get a little bit bored. (I was the latter)The character Rufus is definitely not a typical Hero kind. He is a clumsy, dirty, egocentric, self-centered small town boy with high ambitions. I get irritated sometimes that he is too obvious. Nonetheless, I cannot hate him somehow. Plus he is so funny.For a click adventure game, it is not too easy nor too hard. But sometimes I got stuck in some situations which I needed to take time and try different methods.Overall, It is an interesting game that can be accessed easily by anyone."
