76561198129791148,Recommended,214340,28804409,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,Trainer117,"Are you looking for something to cheer you up but at the same time challenge you? Then look no feather. Deponia is a charming and funny little romp through the trash planet of Deponia. You play as Rufus, a sarcastic, egomaniac, who’s one goal in life is to escape the ball of sewage he calls home and live in the floating city of Elysium. Now that description of the main character may though you off. And I will admit Rufus is a bit of an♥♥♥♥♥and you could easily dislike him. But he’s funny and a little sympathetic to. So I found myself eventually warming up to him. Plus he does start to show signs of change by the end. And this is only the first game in a trilogy so he’s bound to get better. Oh and quick side note, since it is the first game in a trilogy there is a lot of set up but little pay off. Not a deal breaker though, since there was enough to make me want the next one. Now back to Rufus. If you still hate him by the end don’t worry because there’s always another character to pop his ego balloon, leading to some very funny moments. The only negative I have to give this game is that it has a very odd train of thought for some of its puzzles. But a good walkthrough solves that problem. All and all this is a great game with funny duologue and a set of challenging but absurd puzzles."
