76561198014140422,Recommended,214340,20151009,"Posted: 31 December, 2015",all,The Arkady,"""Life's a piece of♥♥♥♥♥♥ when you look at it...""- Monty Python pretty much summed up what living on Deponia is like. So it's no wonder protagonist Rufus wants to escape the literal pile of trash. Too bad he's an obnoxious, egocentric idiot who can barely do anything right, other than perhaps make various things blow up in various faces...A not-entirely-likeable definitely-not-hero for a protagonist is a classic ingredient for adventure gold, and Daedalic followed other parts of time-honored recipes, too. Puzzles from trivial to head-scratchers (the way some of them don't really have good hints for them may be the game's one Achilles heel), a graphics style that fits the comedic tone of the game and is executed well, plus some nifty little tricks that make playing eassier (like quick-warping to sscreen exits).If you think you live in a dump and have it rough, you ain't seen nothing yet and totally need to treat yourself to theDeponiaexperience. Ideally, look for a package deal that includes the sequels - even though this is a full-length adventure, it's really rather open-ended."
