,Not Recommended,214340,32461644,Posted: 15 June,all,CaeruleanDrew,"The controls aren't the best considering this is only a point and clicker. You often have to click multiple time to select something from your inventory, I had to click 7 times before I could pick up the damn parrot. The characters are fine and I think the art style is nice but the game starts to get generally frustrating after a while. It sends you on a load of convoluted fetch quests that are generally boring and take far too long because of the speed of Rufus. The fetch quest style of the game is made extra infuriating by the fact that you have next to no clue about where you're supposed to be going/what you're doing. Your only options are to grab a walk through or talk to every single person, using every single dialogue option.Navigating the world is a pain too. To go from The Crane to The Tunnel, you have to click down from The Crane, Up to the platform and then click The Tunnel, and that's all on one screen. Half the time you either walk to the place you're going but don't actually enter the room or you don't move at all. The music is fine at first but generally gets very repetitive and annoying after a little while, and it took 2 of us half an hour to pack the suitcase so you can imagine that you'd be listening to it for a while. Hearing the dialogue repeat constantly gets physically frustrating and playing the game becomes a task with all fun removed either because you're endlessly confused or you're annoyance at the bugs is greater than the tiny feeling of accomplishment you get from the Steam Achievements popping up at odd times.I'll admit, the animated cutscenes are quite good and some of the jokes aren't too bad but if I knew this game would start out with packing a highly unlikable main characters suitcase and 2 hours of confusion before they make a ""oh, the one thing you didn't pack"" joke, I probably wouldn't have bought it. I will continue to play though incase my judgment is changed and because I refuse to be defeated by this game"
