,Not Recommended,214340,32098921,Posted: 31 May,all,tukkek,"Suffers from the exact same problems as all your classic adventure games of old: from the very first room onwards you'll be looking for small objects that are easy to miss on the screen, trying your inventory items on everything in search for a solution, using game logic to accomplish things that make no sense in the real world and getting stuck without any sort of a hint system for help. It's very sad to see a game released in 2012 hasn't learned anything from its many predecessors.Admittedly, it seems to be lighter on these elements than most old point-and-click games so if you're an old Sierra or Lucas Arts adventure fan this most likely will be a treat, with funny writing, good voice acting, a pleasant art style and an interesting setting. If you don't mind using an external guide (cheating) to get unstuck, I'd also recommend this from my first impression. Myself though, not being a huge adventure fan and only coming in because of a 90% discount,I'm pulling out at the first glance of every single bad design that better modern adventure games try so hard to stay away from."
,Not Recommended,214340,17353728,"Posted: 2 August, 2015",all,SacredKeyLock,"OK.... this is a NO review...I always try to be supportive of even the crappiest game, but this.... is... a bit too much crap for my taste.Before reading, please, if you are a huge fan of Daedalic games, you might find this review offensive.Actually, you WILL find this offensive.Do not read.I warned you.First of all, the MC.GAWD the only reason I ended this game was because I was too anal not to finish. I had lots and LOTS of AFK moments to cool down JUST BECAUSE of the MC. I'd rather play a total villain than this sad excuse for an anti-hero.I even turned off the audio because I hated listening to his dialogues, and yes, I also skipped through all.Next, the NPCs.Seriously, they are just as bad... except for 2 who were ridiculously harassed by the MC. I actually like these 2 and wonder, if the character designers are actually capable of creating these 2 great characters, then why is the MC such a crap??????You have anti-heroes, and you have jerks. I don't see any of the first in this game.Plot was OK. The world setting reminded me of the Japanese manga GUNM : Battle Angel Alita.Graphics are good. A good reminiscence of Monkey Island and Gabriel Knight (the 2D animation versions).Soundtrack.... no idea. I was so irritated by the MC's dialogue etc then I turned off the audio completely except when I needed it to solve puzzles. Even then I didn't register it into mind.Puzzle.The puzzles are FRUSTRATING and does not make sense. Yes, it's a fantasy world which isn't logical in the first place, but  unfortunately for puzzles, you do need logic. Fantasy world or not.The order does not make sense. I know what to do, and IMO it doesn't effect the game whatsoever if we mix up the orders anyway. But nooooooo..... we miss a step, we can't move on.I purchased a LOT of Daedalic games in a shopping binge because I was desperate for a good point-click game.Played 3, finished 2, and not even thinking about 