,Recommended,214340,8159561,"Posted: 20 December, 2013",all,DJ Pon3,"I absolutely loved Deponia! It made me so happy to finally play a point click action adventure game again after what feels like ages! Seriously, when was the last time I played an actual great point click adventure game? King's quest 7? Leisure Suit Larry love for sale? I dunno, it's certainly been a while though.This game is brilliant, 2d point click adventure animation at it's finest! I love the characters, the rude somewhat selfish Rufus as the main character who is a real &^% hole (But has a certain reason behind his actions later in the series), Goal the beautiful inteliigent girl of your dreams who is just out of reach, Toni the hot ex girlfriend you secretly wish you were still with and a wacky assortment of city residents who all seem to think your a loser and need to just vanish off the face of the planet.Your mission is to find a way off deponia and reach a utopia of sorts known as Elysium, where it is known to be a clean beautiful land full of happiness and what not...unlike Deponia in which you start from, litterally a landfill of a world composed of junk on top of junk for miles to see. There are tons of animations way more than any point click adventure I have ever seen and I actually ponder quite a bit as to how long it took the developers to create these games. Either they had a large team or this took quite some time.This game is so impressive, I really hope more people give it a try and keep it alive for years to come."
