,Recommended,214340,19015364,"Posted: 11 November, 2015",all,Hurricane Taylor,"Deponia is set in a world completely over run by garbage, even being used as a junk heap for another world, Elysium. You play as Rufus, a self proclaimed 'inventor' whose only goal in life is to get off of Deponia and enter Elysium.The world itself is gorgeous, the art style is great and the voice acting is fantastic (I was particularly in love with Captain Bozo).However, it has it's problems. The main one being that Rufus is not a likeable character at all. At best he's an antihero. I actually found myself rooting for him to fail at times. The start of the game sees Rufus trying to create a rocket to launch himself onto one of the garbage trucks that tower overhead so he can get onto a transportation system to Elysium. He has to pack a bag first and you find lots of nagging messages around the house left by his roommate. Rufus apparently doesn't do his fair share of the housework. You later find out that his ex girlfriend is actually letting him live there for free, hoping that he'll get his act together, get a job and occasionally pick up after himself and Rufus still rolls his eyes at her and thinks she's a cow?Anyway despite the unlikeable protagonist, the game is fun, the puzzles are interesting, if a little obscure, there are some funny parts in the game, and the rest of the characters are great"
