,Recommended,214340,17306943,"Posted: 30 July, 2015",all,IIIStrife,"Deponia is a point and click adventure puzzle game about a man named Rufus who lives on a ""Planet"" entirely covered in garbage. (I say Planet with quotations simply because the characters state it's on a planet different form a city called Elysium, located high in the sky, presumably in orbit, even if that doesn't work at all). It's set in the future of our time so you could say it fits into Sci-Fi aswell.Either way, Rufus wants to get to Elysium and he's... well he's rather mad, but he has the brains to get out of any situation, including the situation where he's on Deponia, a place he hates more than anybody else.The game takes... well about as long as it's taken to beat it, but unfortunately like all games in the same genre, once you play it, it takes basically 30 minutes tops to beat it again, knowing all the information, even if that's good for a few laughs.When you play this game, in order to beat some part you REALLY gotta think with conventional logic or even like a smart person and I sometimes fail at that, requiring a walkthrough to figure out what to do with some things.The game has alot of tongue-in-cheek humor bits, and even some normal bits of humor. The art style is very nice with great animations, although unfortunately the lip-syncing is sometimes a bit off, like in the start of the game, it's not too big of a deal.The music is also great but if you get stuck, turn it off or you'll hear it again and again. There's not really too much music, variation for music would've helped somewhat. The game has cats at one point and they're miserably adorable.The puzzles are challenging, but ofcourse it's the main reason as to why it takes 30-40 minutes to beat it given all the puzzle answers are given to you.The story is very engaging though, it's easily the best part of this game. I love Rufus' character, the other characters are just as great, all of them very well voiced and even to say the least, they are even interesting people... when looking at main character such as Gizmo, Rufus, Wenzel, etc.I personally loved playing this game start to finished and even after all this time, I still have the puzzles all memorized to heart... mostly.Droggeljug mode is a special mode that makes it extremely difficult if you don't remember dialogue options, or even know how to skip things as literally every word of text and even dialogue is replaced with the word Droggeljug. Just one of them for text, however this would've been nice for dialogue too as it doesn't follow the same thing, causing Droggeljug mode to be deeply irritating. It could be changed by simply having one word per dialogue option instead of it being word for word replacement.Altogether, the game gets an 8/10. It's great fun, has a splendid atmoshpere, world and story, and the characters are nice too.It would score a 10/10 but Droggeljug mode being really annoying as the word that characters say have no variation, it's just one sound clip looped over and over per character, it detracts from it a fair amount in addition to the fact that many items used on something results in the exact same reaction from Rufus in contexts that don't really make any sense for it, and also if the music had some variation, as it will eventually lose it's value as you get stuck (if you're like me, you WILL get stuck at least once) and hear it for many loops of it."
