,Recommended,214340,11074666,"Posted: 4 July, 2014",all,Diabolical_Oblivion,"I purchased Deponia back when they had the big Thanksgiving/Xmas sales when it was a measely few bucks because the art style and some pretty great reviews peaked my interest. I only bought the first game in the series because i wasnt sure i was going to like it and WOW! I wished i had bought the other 2 games with it.The story is great and the game does a good job at telling it so you never at any point feel lost about whats going on. Characters and voice acting is pretty decent. The main character Rufus brings alot of humor to the game along with a hint of arrogance here and there lol. Im really digging the art style. Point and click adventure games has never been my style but Deponia was an exception.There is one and i mean only ONE bad thing about Deponia. It is a very short game. The thing is, is that it is part of a trilogy so that is a plus. Maybe there aim was to give us a little story here and a little story there, who knows? All i know is im wishing i went ahead and bought the next two games while they were on sale! The first play through for me averaged around 8 hours, because the game progression is fairly slow considering the puzzles and the figuring things out as you go. I played through the game a second time to earn my last achievement and was able to blaze through it in just a matter of 2 hours!So the average person should expect anywhere from 10 to 15 hours, but hey....its a pretty awsome 10 hours and the achievements are all easy to get!WARNING! this game will NOT spoon feed you through the story. You will have to pay attention to details and make sure you pick up everything you can along the way. Every item in your inventory WILL get used!! You will occasionally need help by speaking to the various characters and above all, have patience. I ran around in circles a few moments during my initial playthrough. Some places i was completely stumped for awhile until i just started trying to combine items in my inventory.Lasting impression for Deponia. If your a fan of point and click adventures and puzzle type games, you MUST BUY this game!My Rating : 9 out of 10 , because the game felt like it just wasnt long enough. Still though...the purchse is incouraged!"
