,Recommended,214340,13933772,"Posted: 10 January, 2015",all,JudgeB,"Deponia is a great point-and-click adventure game. It has a fantastic art direction, interesting and well fleshed-out characters, a compelling storyline, and many hours worth of gameplay. It's a great series and you won't be disappointed.That being said, let's consider a few of the cons. Deponia suffers from the curse that haunts most point-and-click adventures: puzzle design. Progress in the game fan often consist not in figuring something out, but on clicking on everything, everyone, in every order imaginable. However, this is mostly a fault of the genre as a whole, true of even great masterpieces like Monkey Island, so you probably know if you can handle this kind of thing or not.Another con is the occasional villainous nature of the protagonist. While Rufus is certainly an anti-hero with plenty of personal faults that people will readily point out to him and which he will readily ignore, a few of his actions are simply mean-spirited. People being harmed by his carelessness is fun and good, but on more than one occassion he sets out to deliberately cause serious harms to his friends. This clashes with the rest of his character, and these moments really do stand out.The jokes can occasionally be crude as well. Nothing vulgar, and always humorous in my opinion, but I can also understand if others disapprove.And lastly, as spoiler free as I can say this, the end of the trilogy leaves several major loose ends.That all being said, Deponia was a fantastic experience and one I will readily share with my friends. The humor is clever, the dialogue is well written, the plot well constructed, and the game only improves as it goes on. Buy this game, support the developers, and demand a sequel trilogy, because this series deserves and demands one!"
