,Recommended,214340,12253534,"Posted: 26 September, 2014",all,Fermi,"Deponia is a comedic point & click adventure game very similar to the Lucas Arts classics Monkey Island and Day of the Tentacle.I'm assuming that you are already familiar with the genre, so I'll keep this short and sweet.Pros:  Fluid animation, high resolution graphics, good soundtrack, interesting plot, funny dialog.Cons:  Puzzles are thrown in with arbitrary handicaps and do not contribute to the plot or integrate well.  The writers got lazy a few times and used the item descriptions from looking at an object as the narration when using the item as well.  It gets annoying hearing the same line multiple times when exploring or experimenting.Recommendation: If you like this sort of game, get it.  You can always look up a walkthrough to deal with the puzzles.Warning: This comedy in a later episode gets quite dark.  If you cannot stomach Southpark type humor, then you're better off skipping this trilogy."
