,Recommended,214340,16307838,"Posted: 11 June, 2015",all,Harcile,"It is very good in some ways and not so great in others. I do recommend it, but it could have been a cult classic with a bit more polishing and thought.The artwork is very good. The voice acting is good. The general presentation of the game is good. Sometimes the animations are a bit off - the generic animations of Rufus rarely match the actions he is supposedly doing, but I consider that a very minor gripe and customizing all those animations would take a lot of time.The main problem is the puzzles as many solutions are downright bizarre. It isn't even really the solutions that are the problem. It is the lack of hints. You have to spot and figure most of it all out manually. Whereas in Monkey Island, Guybrush might say a hint when trying to do something that is blocked, the only hinting in Deponia is buried in long dialogs and usually not for the whackiest puzzles.Some items/objects are almost impossible to spot without a helping hand (not provided by the game, I might add).Also the walking around is time consuming. The town centre can take a considerable amount of time to navigate, and sometimes it is a bit clunky to move between areas of a scene that aren't on the same level.Sadly, only the absolutely determined (those prepared to try every item combination and pixel hunt every scene) will complete this without a guide."
