,Recommended,214340,28611408,"Posted: 24 December, 2016",all,Morpheu5,"Deponia is weird and quirky and Rufus is indeed a jerk, but in a good way. Suffice to say, he'll grow on you towards the end, like that fungal infection in your right toenail that you left untreated for too long. But in a good kind of way. It's hard to explain.The game is good, it's hard, and the story is very well developed and told. I have to say I'm not a big fan of what happens with the dowsing rod, but I'm also not sure whether the authors made that choice intentionally, as a nod to old-time adventures, or whether they just thought it was funny to play with the players like that. Either way, it's not the hardest enigma. It's in fact quite obvious, and that makes it even more infuriating, but hey!I played the game almost entirely in German, with Italian subtitles because I don't understand much German. Now, I know and appreciate very much that there is an Italian dubbing, but it's… erhm, let's just say it's wonky. The acting is most of the times lame, and I can't say the same for the German -- or event the English -- dubbing. Still, I appreciate the effort!Overall, I enjoyed almost every bit of the game. The character animations could be better. The team clearly put a lot of effort in the art -- it's beautiful! -- and the cut scenes -- amazing! -- but in the end you are stuck watching the same 6-frames walk cycles over and over, and even other occasional animations aren't that much better.My girlfriend hated Rufus -- but that's kind of the point, I suppose. She left the room and didn't come back until I stopped playing. Oh, well. I'm just glad that people are still making well written and engaging graphical adventures these days!Absolutely recommended if you are a fan of the genre."
