76561198126877860,Recommended,214340,28825324,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,"Quite, Tyni!","Disclaimer: I have not played Deponia in English at all. This review is for the German version only.I can only say that this is a wonderful point-and-click adventure game. The makers very obviously love the genre, love writing, and love every single one of their characters (and they love singing, of course). The attention to detail, the backdrops, and even the ""combine items in inventory"" dialogue are all testament to this. The character animations and cutscenes are spot-on. Personally, I love the art style and the fresh humour most of all.Great place to start if you have never played a point-and-click adventure game before, too."
