,Recommended,214340,31464432,Posted: 30 April,all,Theta,"TL;DRDefinitly worth full price if you are looking for a challenge and ingenious humor and references.Now this is a game that has it all!I really did enjoy this ride, in several aspects. It was gifting and it was entertaining. And I even realized some parts about myself through this game. Self reflection for the win!First off, the story is actually quite entertaining. I now know that there are a series concerning this game, but the first one did it, the bar is set rather high for the sequels at this point. At a first glance the story may seem short, but I can see that there are a lot of work put into the characters, the puzzles and the references. Especially the references.Jesus! I am usually good at references, but this one is actually a challenge, at least in the aspect of encrypted references, secondary and tertiary input references; as this is by all means a very ingenious game. The developers of this one knows their rust!Although some of the jokes loses a bit of their charm due to this. Sure, there are a lot, and I mean a lot 'simpler' jokes, but the more advanced ones kind of gives that impression of 'missing out', you know, when people laugh at something they do not really understand, just to not seem stupid. This game has quite a bit of that.Especially if you are not like me and absorb everything and overanalyze most input.The puzzles are challenging, because they go outside conventional and linear logic and rationality. That is what I meant that this one has everything. You may get through one piece of the overlapping puzzle by means of logic and rational thinking, but there are aspects and parts that are irrational and completely ♥♥♥♥ed up, which may be reached and solved by hardcore levels of intuition, one-in-a-billion luck or just tireless experimenting (or if you are short of time a walkthrough).There was this one puzzle that really got the best of me, I thought it to be a bug, so I reloaded an earlier save and started replay. But intuition struck, amongst severe degrees of anger and disappointment, and I was positive that people behind such a genius game like this would not make such a simple mistake, so I Googled the thing. And I was obviously not the only one to believe this to be a bug. The solution was so simple that people missed it, by (in any way) ignoring one of the simplest functions (although this function was not really explained in the weird tutorial). I am not sure whether to regard this as genial puzzle design or just a play on plays, or my own shortcoming; or all of them at the same time.Apart from that, I like the story. It is the way of every nerd. They believe themselves to be better, hates the surrounding (or 'idiotis') and usually in one way or another wishes them gone, dead or to leave them behind. And because of that loses the Girl; ha! awesome play on words suddenly realized.I know, because I have been there, to the metaphorical Elysium. I am however one of the few people to jump off. As I personally prefer true autenticity found in the lower levels to made up merit in the elite. And this is why I did enjoy this game, it was easy to parallel to my own life in many aspects.Oh yeah, and the music and voice acting is at its moments flawless. Although the music wear out slightly after a while, it is really good. And the voice acting has its ups and downs (lul), but overall it is by all means good enough to set the bar rather high.Goal/Toni - Would befriend Doc and suspect Blackbeard again."
,Recommended,214340,35220035,Posted: 26 September,all,jedi fedi,Good Point and click game!!!!
